{"title_page": "Jiloan Hamad", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Jiloan Hamad\n| image               = Jiloan Hamad 2018 - cropped.jpg\n| image_size          = 250\n| caption             = Hamad with [[Hammarby Fotboll|Hammarby IF]] in 2018\n| fullname            = Jiloan Mohamed Hamad<ref name=\"international\">{{cite web | url=https://svenskfotboll.se/landslag/landslagsdatabas/landslagsspelare/?fplid=301806| title=Landslagsdatabasen: Jiloan Mohamed Hamad| work=Svenskfotboll.se | date=17 April 2017 | accessdate=7 April 2017 | language = Swedish}}</ref>\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1990|11|06|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Baku]], [[Azerbaijan Soviet Socialist Republic|Azerbaijan SSR]], [[Soviet Union]]\n| height              = {{height|m=1.73}}\n| position            = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]]\n| currentclub         = [[HNK Gorica|Gorica]]\n| clubnumber          = 7\n| youthyears1         =           | youthclubs1= [[BK Forward]]\n<!-- LEAGUE GAMES ONLY - When you update this parameter, please update the club-update parameter! -->\n| years1 = 2006\u20132007  | caps1 = 23  | goals1 = 8   | clubs1 = [[BK Forward]]          \n| years2 = 2008\u20132013  | caps2 = 127 | goals2 = 28  | clubs2 = [[Malm\u00f6 FF]]            \n| years3 = 2014\u20132017  | caps3 = 15  | goals3 = 1   | clubs3 = [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|1899 Hoffenheim]]\n| years4 = 2014\u20132017  | caps4 = 6   | goals4 = 0   | clubs4 = \u2192 [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim II|1899 Hoffenheim II]]\n| years5 = 2015       | caps5 = 6   | goals5 = 1   | clubs5 = \u2192 [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]] (loan)\n| years6 = 2017\u20132018  | caps6 = 54  | goals6 = 15  | clubs6 = [[Hammarby Fotboll|Hammarby IF]]\n| years7 = 2019       | caps7 = 11  | goals7 = 1   | clubs7 = [[Incheon United FC|Incheon United]]\n| years8 = 2019\u2013      | caps8 = 3   | goals8 = 1   | clubs8 = [[HNK Gorica|Gorica]]\n| nationalyears1      = 2006\u20132007 | nationalteam1 = [[Sweden national under-17 football team|Sweden U17]] | nationalcaps1 = 9  | nationalgoals1 = 4\n| nationalyears2      = 2007\u20132009 | nationalteam2 = [[Sweden national under-19 football team|Sweden U19]] | nationalcaps2 = 17 | nationalgoals2 = 2\n| nationalyears3      = 2009\u20132012 | nationalteam3 = [[Sweden national under-21 football team|Sweden U21]] | nationalcaps3 = 28 | nationalgoals3 = 3\n| nationalyears4      = 2011\u20132018| nationalteam4 = [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]]              | nationalcaps4 = 8  | nationalgoals4 = 0\n| nationalyears5      = 2019\u2013| nationalteam5 = [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]]              | nationalcaps5 = 1  | nationalgoals5 = 0\n| pcupdate = 29 January 2019\n| ntupdate = 11 January 2018\n}}\n\n'''Jiloan Hamad''' (born 6 November 1990) is a [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for [[HNK Gorica]] in the [[Prva HNL]] and [[Iraq national football team]]. Born in Azerbaijan and of Iraqi descent, Hamad moved to Sweden and represented their national team before switching to represent Iraq.\n\n==Early and personal life==\nHamad was born in [[Azerbaijan]], and is of [[Kurdish people|Kurdish]] descent.<ref name=\"Expressen\">{{cite web | url=http://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/landslaget/hyllar-sin-pappa---trots-hard-uppvaxt/ | title=Hyllar sin pappa - trots h\u00e5rd uppv\u00e4xt | publisher=Expressen | date=23 January 2012 | accessdate=27 October 2014 | author=Kristoffersson, Daniel}}</ref> His family originates from [[Ranya]], [[Iraqi Kurdistan]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://iraqsport.wordpress.com/2013/10/30/jiloan-hamad-can-still-play-for-iraq/ | title = jiloan Hamad can still play for Iraq | publisher = iraqsport.wordpress.com | date = 30 October 2013 | accessdate = 2 January 2014 | first = Hassanin | last = Mubarak}}</ref><ref name=\"Jille n\u00e4ra m\u00e5ls\u00e4ttningen\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mff.se/Aktuellt/Nyhetsarkiv/2009/2009-01-01_Jiloan_Hamad |title=Att f\u00e5 vara en av de tongivande spelarna i MFF skulle k\u00e4nnas h\u00e4ftigt |work=mff.se |date=22 July 2009 |accessdate=7 March 2010 |last=Reimer |first=Arne |language=Swedish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130311043506/http://mff.se/Aktuellt/Nyhetsarkiv/2009/2009-01-01_Jiloan_Hamad |archivedate=11 March 2013 }}</ref> They sought refugee status in both [[Turkmenistan]] and [[Russia]] before settling in [[Sweden]] in 1992, when Jiloan was two years old. Mohammed Hamad, Jiloan's father, was a [[guerrilla warfare|guerrilla warrior]] in the Kurdish [[peshmerga]] for 15 years before fleeing Iraq together with his wife and children.<ref name=\"Jiloan longread\">{{cite web | url=http://jiloanhamad.story.aftonbladet.se/| title=\"Alltid trott stenh\u00e5rt p\u00e5 att jag har mitt \u00f6de i mina egna h\u00e4nder\" | work=Aftonbladet.se | date=25 February 2017 | accessdate=3 April 2017 | last=Niva | first=Erik | language = Swedish}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\n===BK Forward===\nJiloan Hamad started his footballing career at the local club [[BK Forward]] in [[\u00d6rebro]], where he grew up. He debuted in the senior team in 2006, aged 16, when the club competed in the Swedish third tier called [[Division 1 (Swedish football)|Division 1]].<ref name=\"svenskafans\">{{cite web|url=http://www.svenskafans.com/fotboll/jiloan-hamad-min-karlek-for-osk-forsvann-nar-de-sa-att-jag-var-for-liten-567773.aspx|title=Jiloan Hamad: \"min k\u00e4rlek f\u00f6r \u00d6SK f\u00f6rsvann n\u00e4r de sa att jag var f\u00f6r liten\"|date=16 March 2017|accessdate=3 April 2017|publisher=Svenskafans.com}}</ref> During the upcoming two seasons, he played 23 competitive games for the club, scoring 8 goals. During this period, he enjoyed a fruitful partnership with [[Jimmy Durmaz]], his childhood friend who later would move on to play with him at [[Malm\u00f6 FF]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sydsvenskan.se/2017-03-23/durmaz-sagning-av-mff-en-sadan-spelare-tar-man-bara-hem|title=Durmaz s\u00e5gning av MFF: \"En s\u00e5dan spelare tar man bara hem\"|date=23 March 2017|accessdate=3 April 2017|publisher=Svenskafans.com}}</ref> Before switching to the [[Scania]]n team he was refused by the local giants [[\u00d6rebro SK]], with the club citing that Hamad \"was too short\".<ref name=\"svenskafans\"/>\n\n===Malm\u00f6 FF===\n[[File:Jiloan Hamad-2011.png|thumb|Hamad with Malm\u00f6 FF in 2011]]\nHamad came to [[Malm\u00f6 FF]] from BK Forward in December 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/allsvenskan/malmo-ff-varvar-talanger-fran-forward/|title=Malm\u00f6 FF v\u00e4rvar talanger fr\u00e5n Forward|date=9 November 2017|accessdate=15 August 2017|publisher=Fotbollskanalen}}</ref> He made his [[Allsvenskan]] debut on 17 September 2008 in a 0\u20134-loss against [[IF Elfsborg]]. After only having played one match for the club in 2008, Hamad had a breakthrough in 2009 when he played 20 matches and scored two goals. In 2010, he battled with teammate [[Jimmy Durmaz]] for the position as left midfielder. Hamad ended up playing 27 games although only starting in 10, the majority of which were played as right midfielder. In the final game of 2010, he scored the game-winning goal against [[Mj\u00e4llby AIF]] that secured the title, the day after his 20th birthday.\n\nIn [[2011 Allsvenskan|2011]], Hamad started the season with injury problems and missed the start of the season. He recovered and became the natural choice for playing right midfielder after team-mate [[Guillermo Molins]] was sold in the summer transfer window of 2011. Hamad also participated in the club's campaign to qualify for the [[2011\u201312 UEFA Champions League]] and scored the goal that took the club through to the play-off round after equalizing at home against [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]. He continued to play in Europe as the club qualified for the group stage of the [[2011\u201312 UEFA Europa League]] after losing in the play-off round of the Champions League. During the 2011 season Hamad signed a new contract to the end of the 2013 season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mff.se/Aktuellt/Nyheter/2011-04-08_Hamad_klar.aspx |publisher=mff.se |title=Hamad f\u00f6rl\u00e4nger |language=Swedish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111106000903/http://www.mff.se/Aktuellt/Nyheter/2011-04-08_Hamad_klar.aspx |archivedate=6 November 2011 }}</ref>\n\nHamad played all of Malm\u00f6 FF's 30 league matches during the [[2012 Allsvenskan|2012 season]]. He also scored six goals which was his best goal production since joining the club. Hamad was also given the captaincy for the majority of the team's matches. Former captain [[Daniel Andersson (footballer born 1977)|Daniel Andersson]] had stepped down to focus on coaching duties before the beginning of the season and new captain [[Ulrich Vinzents]] received limited time on the pitch.\n\nThe [[2013 Malm\u00f6 FF season|2013 season]] was Hamad's first and only season as full-time captain for the club. In total he played 28 matches and scored eight goals in the league. He also played all matches for the club during the qualification stage for the [[2013\u201314 UEFA Europa League]] and scored two goals. Some of his goals in the early part of the season was match-deciding, on 14 April 2013 he scored the only goal of the game in the home fixture against [[Kalmar FF]], one week later he made the same accomplishment in the away fixture against [[AIK Fotboll|AIK]]. Malm\u00f6 FF secured the title one round before the competition of the league and Hamad could raise [[Lennart Johanssons Pokal]] on 3 November 2013 after a last home win against [[Syrianska FC]]. His last match for the club was the [[2013 Svenska Supercupen]] against [[IFK G\u00f6teborg]] which Malm\u00f6 FF won 3\u20132. For his performances in the [[2013 Allsvenskan]] season he won midfielder of the year and was also nominated for most valuable player of the year.\n\n===TSG 1899 Hoffenheim===\nOn 30 October 2013, German [[Bundesliga]] club [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|1899 Hoffenheim]] confirmed the free transfer of Jiloan Hamad to the club with a contract until 2017.<ref name=\"Hoffenheim\">{{cite web | url=http://www.achtzehn99.de/schwedens-nationalspieler-jiloan-hamad-wechselt-zur-tsg/ | title=Schwedens Nationalspieler Jiloan Hamad wechselt zur TSG | publisher=TSG 1899 Hoffenheim | work=achtzehn99.de | date=30 October 2013 | accessdate=30 October 2013 | language=German}}</ref> The transfer went through on 1 January 2014 when the German transfer window opened. During the same spring he played 8 competitive games for his new side.\n\nAfter attracting a serious injury during his loan spell at [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]] in 2015, he made his comeback for Hoffenheim in a [[Bundesliga]] fixture against [[Bayer Leverkusen]] on 23 January 2016, in which he scored the first goal in a 1-1 draw.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/internationell/tyskland/article22138270.ab | title=Succ\u00e9 f\u00f6r Hamad \u2013 m\u00e5l i comebacken | publisher=Aftonbladet | work=achtzehn99.de | date=23 January 2016 | accessdate=10 February 2017 | language=Swedish}}</ref>\n\n===Standard Li\u00e8ge===\nIn late January 2015, he was loaned to [[Belgian Pro League|Belgian first tier]] side [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]] for the remainder of the 2014\u20132015 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.achtzehn99.de/tsg-loan-out-hamad-and-biteco/ |title=TSG loan out Hamad and Biteco |date=31 January 2015 |accessdate=28 February 2015 |publisher=TSG 1899 Hoffenheim |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150228120310/http://www.achtzehn99.de/tsg-loan-out-hamad-and-biteco/ |archivedate=28 February 2015 }}</ref> He played 6 competitive games for the side, scoring once, before injuring his knee in late March 2015, effectively ending his season.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/article20536841.ab | title=Jiloan Hamad borta resten av s\u00e4songen | publisher=Aftonbladet | work=achtzehn99.de | date=27 March 2015 | accessdate=10 February 2017 | language=Swedish}}</ref>\n\n===Hammarby IF===\nHe returned to his native country on 7 February 2017, signing a two-year deal (with an option for a further) with the [[Stockholm]]-based side [[Hammarby Fotboll|Hammarby IF]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/jiloan-hamad-klar-for-bajen/|title=Jiloan Hamad klar f\u00f6r Bajen|date=7 February 2017|accessdate=7 February 2017|publisher=Hammarby Fotboll}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.achtzehn99.de/news/overview/hamad-joins-hammarby-if/|title=Hamad joins Hammarby IF|date=7 February 2017|accessdate=10 February 2017|publisher=TSG 1889 Hoffenheim}}</ref> Hamad scored two goals in three games as Hammarby got knocked out in the group stage of the [[2016\u201317 Svenska Cupen]]. On 3 April, the first match day of [[2017 Hammarby Fotboll season|Allsvenskan 2017]], he contributed with an assist to [[R\u00f4mulo Cabral Pereira Pinto|R\u00f4mulo]]'s 2\u20131-goal in an away loss against IFK Norrk\u00f6ping.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/utraknat-hif-en-felskriven-slutscen-fran-poang/|title=Utr\u00e4knat HIF en felskriven slutscen fr\u00e5n po\u00e4ng|publisher=Hammarby Fotboll |date=April 2, 2017 |accessdate=April 4, 2017}}</ref> He scored a brace for his side in a 2-1 away win against [[Halmstads BK|Halmstad]] on 14 May.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/lPW6e/jiloan-hamad-matchhjalte-och-skadad|title=Jiloan Hamad matchhj\u00e4lte och skadad|publisher=Aftonbladet |date=May 14, 2017 |accessdate=May 14, 2017}}</ref> Hamad scored his first home goal at [[Tele2 Arena]] on 13 August 2017, from the penalty spot in a 2\u20132 draw against [[\u00d6stersunds FK|\u00d6stersund]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/bittert-men-hoppingivande-kryss-mot-ofk/|title=Bittert men hoppingivande kryss mot \u00d6FK|publisher=Hammarby Fotboll|date=13 August 2017|accessdate=13 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Incheon United===\nOn 29 January 2019, Hamad signed with [[Incheon United FC|Incheon United]] in the [[K League 1]].<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/jiloan-hamad-lamnar-hammarby-tack-for-all-karlek/|title=Jiloan Hamad har gjort klart med ny klubb - \"Tack f\u00f6r all k\u00e4rlek!\"|publisher=Hammarby Fotboll|date=29 January 2019|accessdate=29 January 2019|language=Swedish}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.incheonutd.com/2018/fanzone/feeds_view.php?idx=3358&tgbn=feeds_report|script-title=ko:[\uc785\ub2e8\uc778\ud130\ubdf0] \u2018\ub2e4\uc7ac\ub2e4\ub2a5 \uc5b4\ud0dc\ucee4\u2019 \ud558\ub9c8\ub4dc, \uc778\ucc9c\uc5d0\uc11c\uc758 \uc0c8 \ub3c4\uc804\uc5d0 \uc124\ub818\uc744 \ud45c\ud558\ub2e4|publisher=Incheon United|date=29 January 2019|accessdate=29 January 2019|language=Korean}}</ref> On July 23, 2019 Jiloan Hamad parted ways with Incheon by mutual consent.\n\n==International career==\n\nHaving been born in Azerbaijan, he was able to represent both Iraq, Azerbaijan and Sweden.\n\n===Sweden U21===\n\nHamad was a member and also for some time the captain of the Sweden U21 national side. On 7 September 2010, Hamad scored a [[last-minute goal]] for the 1\u20130 away win against [[Bulgaria national under-21 football team|Bulgaria U21]] in a [[2011 UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship qualification|2011 UEFA Euro U-21 Championship qualifier]]. In early 2011, Hamad revealed that he had rejected an offer from [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]] coach [[Berti Vogts]] to play for his country of birth.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hamad nobbade Azerbadjan |url=http://www.sydsvenskan.se/sport/fotboll/mff/article1344847/Hamad-nobbade-Azerbadjan.html |accessdate=3 February 2011 |newspaper=[[Sydsvenska Dagbladet]] |date=4 January 2011 |language=Swedish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110108101547/http://www.sydsvenskan.se/sport/fotboll/mff/article1344847/Hamad-nobbade-Azerbadjan.html |archivedate= 8 January 2011 }}</ref>\n\n===Sweden===\n\nHamad was first with the [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]] squad for the 2011 January training tour and played his first cap for Sweden during this tour.<ref>{{cite news|last=J\u00f6nsson |first=Kent |title=MFF-dominans i Hamr\u00e9ns trupp |url=http://www.sydsvenskan.se/sport/fotboll/article1327700/Pekalski-och-Hamad-med-i-vinterturn%C3%A9n.html |accessdate=3 February 2011 |newspaper=Sydsvenska Dagbladet |date=14 December 2010 |agency=[[Tidningarnas Telegrambyr\u00e5|TT]] |language=Swedish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110105201124/http://www.sydsvenskan.se/sport/fotboll/article1327700/Pekalski-och-Hamad-med-i-vinterturn%C3%A9n.html |archivedate=5 January 2011 }}</ref>  His first cap for Sweden was against [[Botswana national football team|Botswana]] on 19 January 2011. Hamad was once again selected for the annual training camp for the Sweden national team in January 2012. The squad selection for the camp traditionally features the best Swedish players in domestic and other Scandinavian leagues.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.fotbollskanalen.se/1.2495446/2012/01/12/landslaget_blir_himmelsblagult_vi_ar_stolta|title= Landslaget blir himmelsbl\u00e5gult: \"Vi \u00e4r stolta\"|publisher=Fotbollskanalen|accessdate= 13 January 2012|language=Swedish | first = David B. | last = Larsson}}</ref> He was selected for the friendly against England on 14 November, but did not get any playing time, and was then again selected for the winter tour in 2013.\n\nAfter a five year absence, Hamad was called up to the Swedish squad for the training tour in January 2018. He made his return on the pitch in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]], where several pundits praised Hamad's performance and voted him as the best player on the pitch.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://bloggar.expressen.se/kristoffersson/2018/01/hamad-glanste-i-blagult/|title=Hamad gl\u00e4nste i Bl\u00e5gult|publisher=Expressen|author=Daniel Kristoffersson|date=7 January 2018|accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/Qlx7LV/frustrerande-att-se-hamad-i-abu-dhabi|title=Frustrerande att se Hamad i Abu Dhabi|publisher=Aftonbladet|author=Patrik Brenning|date=7 January 2018|accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/bloggar/lundh/2018/01/07/en-installning-i-januari-som-inte-alltid-varit-given/|title=En inst\u00e4llning i januari som inte alltid varit given|publisher=Fotbollskanalen|author=Olof Lundh|date=7 January 2018|accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Iraq===\nHamad was reported to be called up by [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] in October 2018 though he declined to comment.<ref>https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/landslag/hamad-uppges-aktuell-for-iraks-landslag/</ref> He was not called into Sweden\u2019s squad in December 2018.<ref>https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/bloggar/lundh/2018/12/03/ratt-spelare-pa-vinterturne-men-helt-fel-resmal/</ref> On February 26, 2019, Hamad announced that he will represent the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]] and \"help the team reach new heights\" from February 2019 and onward.<ref>https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/landslag/klart-hamad-byter-till-iraks-landslag-tiden-ar-ratt/</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===Club===\n{{updated|14 November 2018}}<ref name=\"Soccerway\">{{cite web | url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/jiloan-hamad/28091/ | title=Jiloan Hamad | publisher=Soccerway | work=soccerway.com | accessdate=13 January 2013}}</ref>\n<!-- NOTE: when updating stats, update the infobox and add totals too! -->\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[BK Forward]]\n|[[2006 Swedish football Division 1|2006]]\n|0||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||0||0\n|-\n|[[2007 Swedish football Division 1|2007]]\n|23||8||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||23||8\n|-\n!Total\n!23!!8!!0!!0!!colspan=\"2\"|\u2014!!23!!8\n|-\n|rowspan=\"7\"|[[Malm\u00f6 FF]]\n|[[2008 Allsvenskan|2008]]\n|1||0||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||3||0\n|-\n|[[2009 Allsvenskan|2009]]\n|20||2||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||20||2\n|-\n|[[2010 Allsvenskan|2010]]\n|27||3||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||29||3\n|-\n|[[2011 Allsvenskan|2011]]\n|20||3||1||1||11||2||32||6\n|-\n|[[2012 Allsvenskan|2012]]\n|30||6||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||31||6\n|-\n|[[2013 Allsvenskan|2013]]\n|28||8||3||1||6||2||37||11\n|-\n!Total\n!126!!22!!9!!2!!17!!4!!152!!28\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|1899 Hoffenheim]]\n|[[2013\u201314 Bundesliga|2013\u201314]]\n|7||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||8||0\n|-\n|[[2014-15 Bundesliga|2014\u201315]]\n|1||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||1||0\n|-\n|[[2015-16 Bundesliga|2015\u201316]]\n|7||1||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||7||1\n|-\n|[[2016-17 Bundesliga|2016\u201317]]\n|0||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||0||0\n|-\n!Total\n!15!!1!!1!!0!!0!!0!!16!!1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim II|1899 Hoffenheim II]] (loan)\n|[[2013\u201314 Regionalliga|2013\u201314]]\n|1||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||1||0\n|-\n|[[2014-15 Regionalliga|2014\u201315]]\n|2||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||2||0\n|-\n|[[2015-16 Regionalliga|2015\u201316]]\n|2||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||2||0\n|-\n|[[2016-17 Regionalliga|2016\u201317]]\n|1||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||1||0\n|-\n!Total\n!6!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!6!!0\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Standard Li\u00e8ge]] (loan)\n|[[2014\u201315 Belgian Pro League|2014\u201315]]\n|6||1||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||6||1\n|-\n!Total\n!6!!1!!0!!0!!0!!0!!6!!1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Hammarby Fotboll|Hammarby IF]]\n|[[2017 Allsvenskan|2017]]\n|25||4||4||2||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||29||6\n|-\n|[[2018 Allsvenskan|2018]]\n|29||11||4||2||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||33||13\n|-\n!Total\n!54!!15!!8!!4!!0!!0!!62!!19\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Career total\n!230!!47!!18!!6!!17!!4!!265!!57\n|}\n\n===International===\n{{updated|11 January 2018|<ref name=\"Soccerway\" />}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! National team!!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"|[[Sweden national football team|Sweden]]\n|[[2011 in Swedish football|2011]]||2||0\n|-\n|[[2012 in Swedish football|2012]]||2||0\n|-\n|[[2013 in Swedish football|2013]]||2||0\n|-\n|[[2018 in Swedish football|2018]]||2||0\n|-\n! colspan=2|Total!!8!!0\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n<!--Actual awards only; do not include runners-up.-->\n\n===Club===\n;Malm\u00f6 FF\n*[[Allsvenskan]]: [[2010 Allsvenskan|2010]], [[2013 Allsvenskan|2013]]\n*[[Svenska Supercupen]]: [[2013 Svenska Supercupen|2013]]\n\n===Individual===\n*[[Allsvenskan]] midfielder of the year: [[2013 Allsvenskan#Allsvenskans stora pris|2013]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120225091820/http://www.mff.se/Personer/A_truppen/Utespelare/Jiloan_Hamad.aspx Malm\u00f6 FF profile] {{in lang|sv}}\n* {{Svenskfotboll|pid=5689|fid=301806}}\n* {{Soccerway|jiloan-hamad/28091}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-sports}}\n{{succession box| before=[[Ulrich Vinzents]]| title=[[Malm\u00f6 FF]]<br />[[List of Malm\u00f6 FF players#Club captains|Captain]]| years=2013| after=[[Guillermo Molins]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hamad, Jiloan}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Baku]]\n[[Category:Iraqi footballers]]\n[[Category:Iraq international footballers]]\n[[Category:Swedish footballers]]\n[[Category:Sweden youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Sweden under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Sweden international footballers]]\n[[Category:Swedish people of Iraqi descent]]\n[[Category:Swedish people of Kurdish descent]]\n[[Category:BK Forward players]]\n[[Category:Malm\u00f6 FF players]]\n[[Category:TSG 1899 Hoffenheim players]]\n[[Category:Standard Li\u00e8ge players]]\n[[Category:Hammarby Fotboll players]]\n[[Category:Incheon United FC players]]\n[[Category:HNK Gorica players]]\n[[Category:Allsvenskan players]]\n[[Category:Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:K League 1 players]]\n[[Category:Belgian First Division A players]]\n[[Category:Croatian First Football League players]]\n[[Category:Kurdish sportspeople]]\n[[Category:Swedish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Swedish expatriate sportspeople in Germany]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Germany]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Belgium]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Croatia]]\n[[Category:Association football wingers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Jiloan Hamad\n| image               = Jiloan Hamad 2018 - cropped.jpg\n| image_size          = 250\n| caption             = Hamad with [[Hammarby Fotboll|Hammarby IF]] in 2018\n| fullname            = Jiloan Mohamed Hamad<ref name=\"international\">{{cite web | url=https://svenskfotboll.se/landslag/landslagsdatabas/landslagsspelare/?fplid=301806| title=Landslagsdatabasen: Jiloan Mohamed Hamad| work=Svenskfotboll.se | date=17 April 2017 | accessdate=7 April 2017 | language = Swedish}}</ref>\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1990|11|06|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Baku]], [[Azerbaijan Soviet Socialist Republic|Azerbaijan SSR]], [[Soviet Union]]\n| height              = {{height|m=1.73}}\n| position            = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]]\n| currentclub         = [[HNK Gorica|Gorica]]\n| clubnumber          = 7\n| youthyears1         =           | youthclubs1= [[BK Forward]]\n<!-- LEAGUE GAMES ONLY - When you update this parameter, please update the club-update parameter! -->\n| years1 = 2006\u20132007  | caps1 = 23  | goals1 = 8   | clubs1 = [[BK Forward]]          \n| years2 = 2008\u20132013  | caps2 = 127 | goals2 = 28  | clubs2 = [[Malm\u00f6 FF]]            \n| years3 = 2014\u20132017  | caps3 = 15  | goals3 = 1   | clubs3 = [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|1899 Hoffenheim]]\n| years4 = 2014\u20132017  | caps4 = 6   | goals4 = 0   | clubs4 = \u2192 [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim II|1899 Hoffenheim II]]\n| years5 = 2015       | caps5 = 6   | goals5 = 1   | clubs5 = \u2192 [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]] (loan)\n| years6 = 2017\u20132018  | caps6 = 54  | goals6 = 15  | clubs6 = [[Hammarby Fotboll|Hammarby IF]]\n| years7 = 2019       | caps7 = 11  | goals7 = 1   | clubs7 = [[Incheon United FC|Incheon United]]\n| years8 = 2019\u2013      | caps8 = 3   | goals8 = 1   | clubs8 = [[HNK Gorica|Gorica]]\n| nationalyears1      = 2006\u20132007 | nationalteam1 = [[Sweden national under-17 football team|Sweden U17]] | nationalcaps1 = 9  | nationalgoals1 = 4\n| nationalyears2      = 2007\u20132009 | nationalteam2 = [[Sweden national under-19 football team|Sweden U19]] | nationalcaps2 = 17 | nationalgoals2 = 2\n| nationalyears3      = 2009\u20132012 | nationalteam3 = [[Sweden national under-21 football team|Sweden U21]] | nationalcaps3 = 28 | nationalgoals3 = 3\n| nationalyears4      = 2011\u20132018| nationalteam4 = [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]]              | nationalcaps4 = 8  | nationalgoals4 = 0\n| nationalyears5      = 2019\u2013| nationalteam5 = [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]]              | nationalcaps5 = 1  | nationalgoals5 = 0\n| pcupdate = 29 January 2019\n| ntupdate = 11 January 2018\n}}\n\n'''Jiloan Hamad''' (born 6 November 1990) is an [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for [[HNK Gorica]] in the [[Prva HNL]] and [[Iraq national football team]]. Born in Azerbaijan and of Iraqi descent, Hamad moved to Sweden and represented their national team before switching to represent Iraq.\n\n==Early and personal life==\nHamad was born in [[Azerbaijan]], and is of [[Kurdish people|Kurdish]] descent.<ref name=\"Expressen\">{{cite web | url=http://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/landslaget/hyllar-sin-pappa---trots-hard-uppvaxt/ | title=Hyllar sin pappa - trots h\u00e5rd uppv\u00e4xt | publisher=Expressen | date=23 January 2012 | accessdate=27 October 2014 | author=Kristoffersson, Daniel}}</ref> His family originates from [[Ranya]], [[Iraqi Kurdistan]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://iraqsport.wordpress.com/2013/10/30/jiloan-hamad-can-still-play-for-iraq/ | title = jiloan Hamad can still play for Iraq | publisher = iraqsport.wordpress.com | date = 30 October 2013 | accessdate = 2 January 2014 | first = Hassanin | last = Mubarak}}</ref><ref name=\"Jille n\u00e4ra m\u00e5ls\u00e4ttningen\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mff.se/Aktuellt/Nyhetsarkiv/2009/2009-01-01_Jiloan_Hamad |title=Att f\u00e5 vara en av de tongivande spelarna i MFF skulle k\u00e4nnas h\u00e4ftigt |work=mff.se |date=22 July 2009 |accessdate=7 March 2010 |last=Reimer |first=Arne |language=Swedish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130311043506/http://mff.se/Aktuellt/Nyhetsarkiv/2009/2009-01-01_Jiloan_Hamad |archivedate=11 March 2013 }}</ref> They sought refugee status in both [[Turkmenistan]] and [[Russia]] before settling in [[Sweden]] in 1992, when Jiloan was two years old. Mohammed Hamad, Jiloan's father, was a [[guerrilla warfare|guerrilla warrior]] in the Kurdish [[peshmerga]] for 15 years before fleeing Iraq together with his wife and children.<ref name=\"Jiloan longread\">{{cite web | url=http://jiloanhamad.story.aftonbladet.se/| title=\"Alltid trott stenh\u00e5rt p\u00e5 att jag har mitt \u00f6de i mina egna h\u00e4nder\" | work=Aftonbladet.se | date=25 February 2017 | accessdate=3 April 2017 | last=Niva | first=Erik | language = Swedish}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\n===BK Forward===\nJiloan Hamad started his footballing career at the local club [[BK Forward]] in [[\u00d6rebro]], where he grew up. He debuted in the senior team in 2006, aged 16, when the club competed in the Swedish third tier called [[Division 1 (Swedish football)|Division 1]].<ref name=\"svenskafans\">{{cite web|url=http://www.svenskafans.com/fotboll/jiloan-hamad-min-karlek-for-osk-forsvann-nar-de-sa-att-jag-var-for-liten-567773.aspx|title=Jiloan Hamad: \"min k\u00e4rlek f\u00f6r \u00d6SK f\u00f6rsvann n\u00e4r de sa att jag var f\u00f6r liten\"|date=16 March 2017|accessdate=3 April 2017|publisher=Svenskafans.com}}</ref> During the upcoming two seasons, he played 23 competitive games for the club, scoring 8 goals. During this period, he enjoyed a fruitful partnership with [[Jimmy Durmaz]], his childhood friend who later would move on to play with him at [[Malm\u00f6 FF]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sydsvenskan.se/2017-03-23/durmaz-sagning-av-mff-en-sadan-spelare-tar-man-bara-hem|title=Durmaz s\u00e5gning av MFF: \"En s\u00e5dan spelare tar man bara hem\"|date=23 March 2017|accessdate=3 April 2017|publisher=Svenskafans.com}}</ref> Before switching to the [[Scania]]n team he was refused by the local giants [[\u00d6rebro SK]], with the club citing that Hamad \"was too short\".<ref name=\"svenskafans\"/>\n\n===Malm\u00f6 FF===\n[[File:Jiloan Hamad-2011.png|thumb|Hamad with Malm\u00f6 FF in 2011]]\nHamad came to [[Malm\u00f6 FF]] from BK Forward in December 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/allsvenskan/malmo-ff-varvar-talanger-fran-forward/|title=Malm\u00f6 FF v\u00e4rvar talanger fr\u00e5n Forward|date=9 November 2017|accessdate=15 August 2017|publisher=Fotbollskanalen}}</ref> He made his [[Allsvenskan]] debut on 17 September 2008 in a 0\u20134-loss against [[IF Elfsborg]]. After only having played one match for the club in 2008, Hamad had a breakthrough in 2009 when he played 20 matches and scored two goals. In 2010, he battled with teammate [[Jimmy Durmaz]] for the position as left midfielder. Hamad ended up playing 27 games although only starting in 10, the majority of which were played as right midfielder. In the final game of 2010, he scored the game-winning goal against [[Mj\u00e4llby AIF]] that secured the title, the day after his 20th birthday.\n\nIn [[2011 Allsvenskan|2011]], Hamad started the season with injury problems and missed the start of the season. He recovered and became the natural choice for playing right midfielder after team-mate [[Guillermo Molins]] was sold in the summer transfer window of 2011. Hamad also participated in the clubs campaign to qualify for the [[2011\u201312 UEFA Champions League]] and scored the goal that took the club through to the play-off round after equalizing at home against [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]. He continued to play in Europe as the club qualified for the group stage of the [[2011\u201312 UEFA Europa League]] after losing in the play-off round of the Champions League. During the 2011 season Hamad signed a new contract to the end of the 2013 season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mff.se/Aktuellt/Nyheter/2011-04-08_Hamad_klar.aspx |publisher=mff.se |title=Hamad f\u00f6rl\u00e4nger |language=Swedish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111106000903/http://www.mff.se/Aktuellt/Nyheter/2011-04-08_Hamad_klar.aspx |archivedate=6 November 2011 }}</ref>\n\nHamad played all of Malm\u00f6 FF's 30 league matches during the [[2012 Allsvenskan|2012 season]]. He also scored six goals which was his best goal production since joining the club. Hamad was also given the captaincy for the majority of the teams matches. Former captain [[Daniel Andersson (footballer born 1977)|Daniel Andersson]] had stepped down to focus on coaching duties before the beginning of the season and new captain [[Ulrich Vinzents]] received limited time on the pitch.\n\nThe [[2013 Malm\u00f6 FF season|2013 season]] was Hamad's first and only season as full-time captain for the club. In total he played 28 matches and scored eight goals in the league. He also played all matches for the club during the qualification stage for the [[2013\u201314 UEFA Europa League]] and scored two goals. Some of his goals in the early part of the season was match-deciding, on 14 April 2013 he scored the only goal of the game in the home fixture against [[Kalmar FF]], one week later he made the same accomplishment in the away fixture against [[AIK Fotboll|AIK]]. Malm\u00f6 FF secured the title one round before the competition of the league and Hamad could raise [[Lennart Johanssons Pokal]] on 3 November 2013 after a last home win against [[Syrianska FC]]. His last match for the club was the [[2013 Svenska Supercupen]] against [[IFK G\u00f6teborg]] which Malm\u00f6 FF won 3\u20132. For his performances in the [[2013 Allsvenskan]] season he won midfielder of the year and was also nominated for most valuable player of the year.\n\n===TSG 1899 Hoffenheim===\nOn 30 October 2013, German [[Bundesliga]] club [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|1899 Hoffenheim]] confirmed the free transfer of Jiloan Hamad to the club with a contract until 2017.<ref name=\"Hoffenheim\">{{cite web | url=http://www.achtzehn99.de/schwedens-nationalspieler-jiloan-hamad-wechselt-zur-tsg/ | title=Schwedens Nationalspieler Jiloan Hamad wechselt zur TSG | publisher=TSG 1899 Hoffenheim | work=achtzehn99.de | date=30 October 2013 | accessdate=30 October 2013 | language=German}}</ref> The transfer went through on 1 January 2014 when the German transfer window opened. During the same spring he played 8 competitive games for his new side.\n\nAfter attracting a serious injury during his loan spell at [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]] in 2015, he made his comeback for Hoffenheim in a [[Bundesliga]] fixture against [[Bayer Leverkusen]] on 23 January 2016, in which he scored the first goal in a 1-1 draw.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/internationell/tyskland/article22138270.ab | title=Succ\u00e9 f\u00f6r Hamad \u2013 m\u00e5l i comebacken | publisher=Aftonbladet | work=achtzehn99.de | date=23 January 2016 | accessdate=10 February 2017 | language=Swedish}}</ref>\n\n===Standard Li\u00e8ge===\nIn late January 2015, he was loaned to [[Belgian Pro League|Belgian first tier]] side [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]] for the remainder of the 2014\u20132015 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.achtzehn99.de/tsg-loan-out-hamad-and-biteco/ |title=TSG loan out Hamad and Biteco |date=31 January 2015 |accessdate=28 February 2015 |publisher=TSG 1899 Hoffenheim |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150228120310/http://www.achtzehn99.de/tsg-loan-out-hamad-and-biteco/ |archivedate=28 February 2015 }}</ref> He played 6 competitive games for the side, scoring once, before injuring his knee in late March 2015, effectively ending his season.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/article20536841.ab | title=Jiloan Hamad borta resten av s\u00e4songen | publisher=Aftonbladet | work=achtzehn99.de | date=27 March 2015 | accessdate=10 February 2017 | language=Swedish}}</ref>\n\n===Hammarby IF===\nHe returned to his native country on 7 February 2017, signing a two-year deal (with an option for a further) with the [[Stockholm]]-based side [[Hammarby Fotboll|Hammarby IF]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/jiloan-hamad-klar-for-bajen/|title=Jiloan Hamad klar f\u00f6r Bajen|date=7 February 2017|accessdate=7 February 2017|publisher=Hammarby Fotboll}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.achtzehn99.de/news/overview/hamad-joins-hammarby-if/|title=Hamad joins Hammarby IF|date=7 February 2017|accessdate=10 February 2017|publisher=TSG 1889 Hoffenheim}}</ref> Hamad scored two goals in three games as Hammarby got knocked out in the group stage of the [[2016\u201317 Svenska Cupen]]. On 3 April, the first match day of [[2017 Hammarby Fotboll season|Allsvenskan 2017]], he contributed with an assist to [[R\u00f4mulo Cabral Pereira Pinto|R\u00f4mulo]]'s 2\u20131-goal in an away loss against IFK Norrk\u00f6ping.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/utraknat-hif-en-felskriven-slutscen-fran-poang/|title=Utr\u00e4knat HIF en felskriven slutscen fr\u00e5n po\u00e4ng|publisher=Hammarby Fotboll |date=April 2, 2017 |accessdate=April 4, 2017}}</ref> He scored a brace for his side in a 2-1 away win against [[Halmstads BK|Halmstad]] on 14 May.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/lPW6e/jiloan-hamad-matchhjalte-och-skadad|title=Jiloan Hamad matchhj\u00e4lte och skadad|publisher=Aftonbladet |date=May 14, 2017 |accessdate=May 14, 2017}}</ref> Hamad scored his first home goal at [[Tele2 Arena]] on 13 August 2017, from the penalty spot in a 2\u20132 draw against [[\u00d6stersunds FK|\u00d6stersund]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/bittert-men-hoppingivande-kryss-mot-ofk/|title=Bittert men hoppingivande kryss mot \u00d6FK|publisher=Hammarby Fotboll|date=13 August 2017|accessdate=13 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Incheon United===\nOn 29 January 2019, Hamad signed with [[Incheon United FC|Incheon United]] in the [[K League 1]].<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/jiloan-hamad-lamnar-hammarby-tack-for-all-karlek/|title=Jiloan Hamad har gjort klart med ny klubb - \"Tack f\u00f6r all k\u00e4rlek!\"|publisher=Hammarby Fotboll|date=29 January 2019|accessdate=29 January 2019|language=Swedish}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.incheonutd.com/2018/fanzone/feeds_view.php?idx=3358&tgbn=feeds_report|script-title=ko:[\uc785\ub2e8\uc778\ud130\ubdf0] \u2018\ub2e4\uc7ac\ub2e4\ub2a5 \uc5b4\ud0dc\ucee4\u2019 \ud558\ub9c8\ub4dc, \uc778\ucc9c\uc5d0\uc11c\uc758 \uc0c8 \ub3c4\uc804\uc5d0 \uc124\ub818\uc744 \ud45c\ud558\ub2e4|publisher=Incheon United|date=29 January 2019|accessdate=29 January 2019|language=Korean}}</ref> On July 23rd, 2019 Jiloan Hamad parted ways with Incheon by mutual consent.\n\n==International career==\n\nHaving been born in Azerbaijan, he was able to represent both Iraq, Azerbaijan and Sweden.\n\n===Sweden U21===\n\nHamad was a member and also for some time the captain of the Sweden U21 national side. On 7 September 2010, Hamad scored a [[last-minute goal]] for the 1\u20130 away win against [[Bulgaria national under-21 football team|Bulgaria U21]] in a [[2011 UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship qualification|2011 UEFA Euro U-21 Championship qualifier]]. In early 2011, Hamad revealed that he had rejected an offer from [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]] coach [[Berti Vogts]] to play for his country of birth.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hamad nobbade Azerbadjan |url=http://www.sydsvenskan.se/sport/fotboll/mff/article1344847/Hamad-nobbade-Azerbadjan.html |accessdate=3 February 2011 |newspaper=[[Sydsvenska Dagbladet]] |date=4 January 2011 |language=Swedish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110108101547/http://www.sydsvenskan.se/sport/fotboll/mff/article1344847/Hamad-nobbade-Azerbadjan.html |archivedate= 8 January 2011 }}</ref>\n\n===Sweden===\n\nHamad was first with the [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]] squad for the 2011 January training tour and played his first cap for Sweden during this tour.<ref>{{cite news|last=J\u00f6nsson |first=Kent |title=MFF-dominans i Hamr\u00e9ns trupp |url=http://www.sydsvenskan.se/sport/fotboll/article1327700/Pekalski-och-Hamad-med-i-vinterturn%C3%A9n.html |accessdate=3 February 2011 |newspaper=Sydsvenska Dagbladet |date=14 December 2010 |agency=[[Tidningarnas Telegrambyr\u00e5|TT]] |language=Swedish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110105201124/http://www.sydsvenskan.se/sport/fotboll/article1327700/Pekalski-och-Hamad-med-i-vinterturn%C3%A9n.html |archivedate=5 January 2011 }}</ref>  His first cap for Sweden was against [[Botswana national football team|Botswana]] on 19 January 2011. Hamad was once again selected for the annual training camp for the Sweden national team in January 2012. The squad selection for the camp traditionally features the best Swedish players in domestic and other Scandinavian leagues.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.fotbollskanalen.se/1.2495446/2012/01/12/landslaget_blir_himmelsblagult_vi_ar_stolta|title= Landslaget blir himmelsbl\u00e5gult: \"Vi \u00e4r stolta\"|publisher=Fotbollskanalen|accessdate= 13 January 2012|language=Swedish | first = David B. | last = Larsson}}</ref> He was selected for the friendly against England on 14 November, but did not get any playing time, and was then again selected for the winter tour in 2013.\n\nAfter a five year absence, Hamad was called up to the Swedish squad for the training tour in January 2018. He made his return on the pitch in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]], where several pundits praised Hamad's performance and voted him as the best player on the pitch.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://bloggar.expressen.se/kristoffersson/2018/01/hamad-glanste-i-blagult/|title=Hamad gl\u00e4nste i Bl\u00e5gult|publisher=Expressen|author=Daniel Kristoffersson|date=7 January 2018|accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/Qlx7LV/frustrerande-att-se-hamad-i-abu-dhabi|title=Frustrerande att se Hamad i Abu Dhabi|publisher=Aftonbladet|author=Patrik Brenning|date=7 January 2018|accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/bloggar/lundh/2018/01/07/en-installning-i-januari-som-inte-alltid-varit-given/|title=En inst\u00e4llning i januari som inte alltid varit given|publisher=Fotbollskanalen|author=Olof Lundh|date=7 January 2018|accessdate=7 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Iraq===\nHamad was reported to be called up by [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] in October 2018 though he declined to comment.<ref>https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/landslag/hamad-uppges-aktuell-for-iraks-landslag/</ref> He was not called into Sweden\u2019s squad in December 2018.<ref>https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/bloggar/lundh/2018/12/03/ratt-spelare-pa-vinterturne-men-helt-fel-resmal/</ref> On February 26, 2019, Hamad announced that he will represent the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]] and \"help the team reach new heights\" from February 2019 and onward.<ref>https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/landslag/klart-hamad-byter-till-iraks-landslag-tiden-ar-ratt/</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===Club===\n{{updated|14 November 2018}}<ref name=\"Soccerway\">{{cite web | url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/jiloan-hamad/28091/ | title=Jiloan Hamad | publisher=Soccerway | work=soccerway.com | accessdate=13 January 2013}}</ref>\n<!-- NOTE: when updating stats, update the infobox and add totals too! -->\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[BK Forward]]\n|[[2006 Swedish football Division 1|2006]]\n|0||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||0||0\n|-\n|[[2007 Swedish football Division 1|2007]]\n|23||8||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||23||8\n|-\n!Total\n!23!!8!!0!!0!!colspan=\"2\"|\u2014!!23!!8\n|-\n|rowspan=\"7\"|[[Malm\u00f6 FF]]\n|[[2008 Allsvenskan|2008]]\n|1||0||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||3||0\n|-\n|[[2009 Allsvenskan|2009]]\n|20||2||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||20||2\n|-\n|[[2010 Allsvenskan|2010]]\n|27||3||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||29||3\n|-\n|[[2011 Allsvenskan|2011]]\n|20||3||1||1||11||2||32||6\n|-\n|[[2012 Allsvenskan|2012]]\n|30||6||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||31||6\n|-\n|[[2013 Allsvenskan|2013]]\n|28||8||3||1||6||2||37||11\n|-\n!Total\n!126!!22!!9!!2!!17!!4!!152!!28\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|1899 Hoffenheim]]\n|[[2013\u201314 Bundesliga|2013\u201314]]\n|7||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||8||0\n|-\n|[[2014-15 Bundesliga|2014\u201315]]\n|1||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||1||0\n|-\n|[[2015-16 Bundesliga|2015\u201316]]\n|7||1||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||7||1\n|-\n|[[2016-17 Bundesliga|2016\u201317]]\n|0||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||0||0\n|-\n!Total\n!15!!1!!1!!0!!0!!0!!16!!1\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim II|1899 